00:56:12,680 --> 00:56:14,960
And the whites in our neighborhood,

990
00:56:14,960 --> 00:56:16,800
they had acted also.

991
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:18,520
So no.

992
00:56:18,560 --> 00:56:22,640
But it did surprise me to have white instructors

993
00:56:22,640 --> 00:56:24,720
with all the black students.

994
00:56:24,720 --> 00:56:26,640
And that may have been a handful of white students

995
00:56:26,640 --> 00:56:30,200
at that time, if I remember correctly, it's kind of hard to tell.

996
00:56:30,200 --> 00:56:34,320
And the president was president Warren.

997
00:56:34,320 --> 00:56:36,400
And I think he was handicapped.

998
00:56:36,400 --> 00:56:38,160
I think he was.

999
00:56:38,160 --> 00:56:40,760
I don't really know much about two right at that time.

1000
00:56:40,760 --> 00:56:46,760
And a couple of my teachers were one of my know was white.

1001
00:56:46,760 --> 00:56:47,480
Yeah.

1002
00:56:47,480 --> 00:56:49,480
Were they from other parts of the country?

1003
00:56:49,480 --> 00:56:50,360
Or were they local?

1004
00:56:50,360 --> 00:56:50,960
I don't know.

1005
00:56:50,960 --> 00:56:51,480
You don't know.

1006
00:56:51,480 --> 00:56:53,960
No, man.

1007
00:56:53,960 --> 00:56:57,840
I had meant to ask you before, was your father

1008
00:56:57,840 --> 00:57:01,480
registered to vote when you were younger?

1009
00:57:01,480 --> 00:57:02,640
No.

1010
00:57:02,640 --> 00:57:04,440
Was he ever able to register?

1011
00:57:04,440 --> 00:57:05,000
No.

1012
00:57:05,000 --> 00:57:06,600
I know some people were registered.

1013
00:57:06,600 --> 00:57:08,040
And then they took them off the rolls.

1014
00:57:08,040 --> 00:57:10,800
And then they had to try to re-register.

1015
00:57:10,800 --> 00:57:12,200
No.

1016
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:14,800
My dad was very conscious of the fact

1017
00:57:14,800 --> 00:57:21,720
that he was being denied the same opportunity as whites.

1018
00:57:21,720 --> 00:57:24,280
And he didn't hide that from us.

1019
00:57:24,280 --> 00:57:25,040
He didn't.

1020
00:57:25,040 --> 00:57:27,720
He depended on them for survival.

1021
00:57:27,720 --> 00:57:30,120
And he never did talk mean about them.

1022
00:57:30,120 --> 00:57:35,200
But he let us know that there was a difference in survival.

1023
00:57:35,200 --> 00:57:39,360
And he would tell us, boys, he said, you got to be twice as good

1024
00:57:39,360 --> 00:57:40,320
to stay out of trouble.

1025
00:57:40,320 --> 00:57:44,640
You got to work twice as hard to get ahead.

1026
00:57:44,640 --> 00:57:46,080
It's not even.

1027
00:57:46,080 --> 00:57:49,280
And he let you know that upfront, it is not even.

1028
00:57:49,280 --> 00:57:51,760
And that helped a lot when I went in the air force.

1029
00:57:51,760 --> 00:57:53,160
Because I felt a little inferior.

1030
00:57:53,160 --> 00:57:55,920
Because I think the white kids went out of these superior

1031
00:57:55,920 --> 00:57:56,920
schools.

1032
00:57:56,920 --> 00:57:59,000
But after a while, I found out, well, yeah, they

1033
00:57:59,000 --> 00:58:01,240
made a came out of superior institution.

1034
00:58:01,240 --> 00:58:04,080
But someone was smarter than me.

1035
00:58:04,080 --> 00:58:05,280
Oh, kids.

1036
00:58:05,280 --> 00:58:08,840
But anyway, at least I didn't think there were any way.

1037
00:58:08,840 --> 00:58:14,040
So I lost my thought.

1038
00:58:14,120 --> 00:58:17,000
Well, I had asked you about your dad trying to vote.

1039
00:58:17,000 --> 00:58:17,840
Oh, yeah.

1040
00:58:17,840 --> 00:58:22,640
So in growing up in that environment,

1041
00:58:22,640 --> 00:58:29,640
my dad paid very close attention to what was going on around

1042
00:58:29,640 --> 00:58:30,840
him, like my grandfather.

1043
00:58:30,840 --> 00:58:33,000
He had newspaper every day.

1044
00:58:33,000 --> 00:58:35,640
We didn't have electricity in the house

1045
00:58:35,640 --> 00:58:39,520
until I was probably in the eighth grade.

1046
00:58:39,520 --> 00:58:42,520
And we stood by light.

1047
00:58:42,520 --> 00:58:45,520
And my dad bought a small radio, RCA,

1048
00:58:45,520 --> 00:58:48,080
one of the old-fashioned kind.

1049
00:58:48,080 --> 00:58:52,640
And so he could listen to the news in other programs.

1050
00:58:52,640 --> 00:58:57,200
And he would drive the school bus up to the window of the house

1051
00:58:57,200 --> 00:59:01,360
and drew the power from the truck battery to run the radio.

1052
00:59:01,360 --> 00:59:02,480
And that's how he'd listen to radio.

1053
00:59:02,480 --> 00:59:05,920
And there were three things that he'd listen to religiously.

1054
00:59:05,920 --> 00:59:08,640
One up in the evenings, at 6 o'clock news,

1055
00:59:08,640 --> 00:59:11,680
with John Cameron Swasey.

1056
00:59:11,680 --> 00:59:16,360
Because he'd make us sit down and be quiet and hear the news.

1057
00:59:16,360 --> 00:59:20,240
If you want to change that, so just let me know.

1058
00:59:20,240 --> 00:59:21,320
OK.

1059
00:59:21,320 --> 00:59:26,360
And everybody, the news is on.

1060
00:59:26,360 --> 00:59:27,360
He didn't have to tell you.

1061
00:59:27,360 --> 00:59:29,520
News on, you be quiet and you listen.

1062
00:59:29,520 --> 00:59:31,920
You didn't leave the room.

1063
00:59:31,920 --> 00:59:33,440
He listened to Loman Abna.

1064
00:59:33,440 --> 00:59:38,280
They came on every day if you ever heard a Loman Abna.

1065
00:59:38,280 --> 00:59:40,800
OK, that was a comedy show of Hillbillies.

1066
00:59:41,800 --> 00:59:44,760
They came on every day on the Loman Abna,

1067
00:59:44,760 --> 00:59:46,760
and then the jot them down store in the country.

1068
00:59:46,760 --> 00:59:47,760
Yeah.

1069
00:59:47,760 --> 00:59:54,640
And Amos and Andy at 6 o'clock in evening.

1070
00:59:54,640 --> 00:59:57,560
And on a Saturday night, he would listen to the grand old

1071
00:59:57,560 --> 00:59:59,520
opera.

1072
00:59:59,520 --> 01:00:01,360
So that was the big entertainment?

1073
01:00:01,360 --> 01:00:02,840
That big entertainment.

1074
01:00:02,840 --> 01:00:04,240
So you got news?

1075
01:00:04,240 --> 01:00:04,760
Right.

1076
01:00:04,760 --> 01:00:05,640
And a couple of shows.

1077
01:00:05,640 --> 01:00:10,200
But as resolved, or paying attention in keeping up with the news,

1078
01:00:10,200 --> 01:00:15,160
we all became news listeners.

1079
01:00:15,160 --> 01:00:15,920
OK.

1080
01:00:15,920 --> 01:00:16,680
Influence.

1081
01:00:16,680 --> 01:00:17,880
Influence.

1082
01:00:17,880 --> 01:00:21,240
And we found out that's where you get your information from.

1083
01:00:21,240 --> 01:00:23,440
My dad had another saying, once we got

1084
01:00:23,440 --> 01:00:25,240
beaten up on the sandwich, talking about,

1085
01:00:25,240 --> 01:00:29,360
he said, pay attention to what's going on around you.

1086
01:00:29,360 --> 01:00:33,040
And you have a chance to get away without being

1087
01:00:33,040 --> 01:00:36,560
a victim of your search circumstances.

1088
01:00:36,560 --> 01:00:38,120
In other words, don't be a victim of your environment

1089
01:00:38,120 --> 01:00:39,720
because you're not paying attention.

1090
01:00:39,720 --> 01:00:42,080
Then he had a parable he used.

1091
01:00:42,080 --> 01:00:46,960
Don't be like a hog eating acres on a big oak tree.

1092
01:00:46,960 --> 01:00:48,840
You eat an acreage, but you never look up

1093
01:00:48,840 --> 01:00:50,880
to see where they are coming from.

1094
01:00:50,880 --> 01:00:54,600
And then when the acres run out and you're hungry,

1095
01:00:54,600 --> 01:00:55,920
you left the stop to death.

1096
01:00:55,920 --> 01:00:58,760
So be aware what's going on around you.

1097
01:00:58,760 --> 01:01:00,800
And that's just where we all grew up.

1098
01:01:00,800 --> 01:01:04,600
All of us are very political oriented, OK?

1099
01:01:04,600 --> 01:01:05,920
Very much so.

1100
01:01:05,920 --> 01:01:08,280
So we came up in a political environment.

1101
01:01:08,280 --> 01:01:15,480
So when in the mid 1940s, my dad had heard about the NAACP

1102
01:01:15,480 --> 01:01:17,840
started up, OK?

1103
01:01:17,840 --> 01:01:24,360
And he and eight other black men

1104
01:01:24,360 --> 01:01:28,360
established the farest-counter branch of the NAACP.

1105
01:01:28,360 --> 01:01:30,160
It was nine of them that started it.

1106
01:01:30,160 --> 01:01:31,800
And they held secret meetings.

1107
01:01:31,800 --> 01:01:34,320
And they went to the meetings at night.

1108
01:01:34,320 --> 01:01:39,120
The nine black men in the Hattensperf area

1109
01:01:39,120 --> 01:01:44,000
that founded the farest-counter branch of the NAACP.

1110
01:01:44,000 --> 01:01:50,600
And it was around 1945, the mid 1940s, OK?

1111
01:01:50,600 --> 01:01:54,440
And at that time, they had the meetings at night.

1112
01:01:54,440 --> 01:01:58,080
And my dad would always let us know, let me know.

1113
01:01:58,080 --> 01:02:00,400
I'm going to NAACP meeting because it

1114
01:02:00,400 --> 01:02:04,600
was an underground type organization on that time.

1115
01:02:04,600 --> 01:02:10,480
And he continued to go to these meetings very religiously.

1116
01:02:10,480 --> 01:02:15,400
And then when he go to the meeting, he would come home

1117
01:02:15,400 --> 01:02:16,600
and we'd be working there.

1118
01:02:16,600 --> 01:02:19,680
And he'd tell us, tell me and my whole brother

1119
01:02:19,680 --> 01:02:23,960
what was going on as we did our work, all right?

1120
01:02:23,960 --> 01:02:34,040
And as a result of him being a part of that organization,

1121
01:02:34,040 --> 01:02:37,760
and he let us know by just a conversation

1122
01:02:37,760 --> 01:02:42,440
that there was, it had something to do with politics.

1123
01:02:42,440 --> 01:02:42,760
OK?

1124
01:02:42,760 --> 01:02:46,120
It had something to do with voting, OK?

1125
01:02:46,120 --> 01:02:57,800
So in about 1946, yeah, I think I was around 16, 17 years old, maybe.

1126
01:02:57,800 --> 01:03:03,120
My dad started taking me with him even before then when he did business.

1127
01:03:03,120 --> 01:03:06,840
I'd go with him when he paid the property tax.

1128
01:03:06,840 --> 01:03:10,520
And at the same time, you paid the property tax to the sheriff.

1129
01:03:10,520 --> 01:03:14,160
Sheriff was a tax collector in Faris County.

1130
01:03:14,160 --> 01:03:17,720
He would also pay his poll tax.

1131
01:03:17,720 --> 01:03:19,520
And when he leave the sheriff's office,

1132
01:03:19,520 --> 01:03:23,480
he'd go down the hall to the voter registration office

1133
01:03:23,480 --> 01:03:26,040
and pay his poll tax.

1134
01:03:26,040 --> 01:03:31,960
Well, on this one occasion, he went to pay the poll tax.

1135
01:03:31,960 --> 01:03:35,360
And may have been the first, I don't know what happened, proud to then.

1136
01:03:35,360 --> 01:03:36,160
He went then.

1137
01:03:36,160 --> 01:03:37,560
He pulled out his receipt.

1138
01:03:37,560 --> 01:03:39,120
He had his hand.

1139
01:03:39,120 --> 01:03:43,040
And there was this white man behind the counter.

1140
01:03:43,040 --> 01:03:47,760
And he walked up me asking, I knew who my dad was, I don't know, being a country town.

1141
01:03:47,760 --> 01:03:48,880
Yeah, what do you want?

1142
01:03:48,880 --> 01:03:50,280
That's how I paid my poll tax.

1143
01:03:50,280 --> 01:03:52,800
I want to register.

1144
01:03:52,800 --> 01:03:54,800
And he looked at him.

1145
01:03:54,800 --> 01:03:57,720
It's just kind of like staring at him, you know, why are you here?

1146
01:03:57,720 --> 01:04:01,400
I remember that because I'm old enough not to know how you treat my dad.

1147
01:04:01,400 --> 01:04:09,000
And he gave my dad a card, like a full-baked card, a six-bate, and he had some writing on it.

1148
01:04:09,000 --> 01:04:10,360
He said, read that and tell me what to say.

1149
01:04:10,360 --> 01:04:12,920
And then he went on back and said, I'm.

1150
01:04:12,920 --> 01:04:16,320
My dad read the information on the card.

1151
01:04:16,320 --> 01:04:20,400
And finally, he says, sir, I'm finished.

1152
01:04:20,400 --> 01:04:23,280
And the guy came up and looked at him and looked at him.

1153
01:04:23,280 --> 01:04:24,520
He said, all right, tell me what you read.

1154
01:04:24,520 --> 01:04:26,040
My dad told him.

1155
01:04:26,040 --> 01:04:27,840
He says that's not what he said.

1156
01:04:27,840 --> 01:04:29,520
And that was end of it.

1157
01:04:29,520 --> 01:04:35,320
Now, here's a man, my father, who had helped me with my lesson.

1158
01:04:35,320 --> 01:04:36,880
He was in business.

1159
01:04:36,880 --> 01:04:38,360
He was running a business.

1160
01:04:38,360 --> 01:04:40,160
And he couldn't interpret what was on the card.

1161
01:04:40,160 --> 01:04:42,480
Now, I was old enough to know that's not true.

1162
01:04:42,480 --> 01:04:44,160
That aggravated me so.

1163
01:04:44,160 --> 01:04:48,800
Because what you did, you just denied a man that I cared a lot about.

1164
01:04:48,800 --> 01:04:53,000
Hey, you just told him, you don't know what you're talking about.

1165
01:04:53,000 --> 01:04:54,560
That didn't hit me very well.

1166
01:04:54,560 --> 01:05:00,760
Now, I didn't get mad about it, but I saw that as strange because I'd never seen this up front that close.

1167
01:05:00,760 --> 01:05:03,560
I'm sure it's happened other places.

1168
01:05:03,560 --> 01:05:11,480
And from that time on, he may have continued.

1169
01:05:11,480 --> 01:05:17,680
I didn't go with him anymore, but I don't know what he did or did not.

1170
01:05:17,680 --> 01:05:24,440
And the next time I heard anything about him becoming involved was when he became president

1171
01:05:24,440 --> 01:05:31,120
of the local NAACB during the mid-50s.

1172
01:05:31,120 --> 01:05:38,160
And as a result of the Supreme Court ruling on the school segregation problem, I was at

1173
01:05:38,160 --> 01:05:40,160
Brown versus Board Education in Kansas.

1174
01:05:40,160 --> 01:05:41,160
Something like that.

1175
01:05:41,160 --> 01:05:43,000
I think that's right.

1176
01:05:43,000 --> 01:05:45,160
Mississippi then tightened up.

1177
01:05:45,160 --> 01:05:47,160
It really tightened up.

1178
01:05:47,160 --> 01:05:49,160
Hey, we're not going to have no school integration here.

1179
01:05:49,160 --> 01:05:52,800
My days already involved in the NAACB by then.

1180
01:05:52,800 --> 01:05:54,720
And he's out of the closet.

1181
01:05:54,720 --> 01:05:56,480
The organization is out of the closet.

1182
01:05:56,480 --> 01:05:57,960
It's well known.

1183
01:05:57,960 --> 01:06:08,000
And then that's when he became targeted by the hostile forces out there.

1184
01:06:08,000 --> 01:06:11,880
What is that first incident that you saw or the one that you witnessed?

1185
01:06:11,880 --> 01:06:14,640
Did he say anything to you when you were riding home that day?

1186
01:06:14,640 --> 01:06:15,640
Did he say anything to you?

1187
01:06:15,640 --> 01:06:16,640
Did he talk to you about what happened?

1188
01:06:16,640 --> 01:06:17,640
No, he did not.

1189
01:06:17,640 --> 01:06:18,640
No.

1190
01:06:18,640 --> 01:06:23,080
I think, going that time, I can only think that that was such a routine practice of being

1191
01:06:23,080 --> 01:06:24,080
denied.

1192
01:06:24,080 --> 01:06:29,480
Maybe he would not be there to him, so maybe he'd go with other blacks.

1193
01:06:29,480 --> 01:06:31,320
He just suck it up and move on.

1194
01:06:31,320 --> 01:06:33,320
Yeah.

1195
01:06:33,320 --> 01:06:38,320
And you said when he was president in the mid-1950s, people knew who he was.

1196
01:06:38,320 --> 01:06:40,840
Oh, yeah, without a doubt.

1197
01:06:40,840 --> 01:06:43,440
And you said that's when the harassment started.

1198
01:06:43,440 --> 01:06:44,440
Yeah.

1199
01:06:44,440 --> 01:06:46,440
That's when the harassment started then, okay?

1200
01:06:46,440 --> 01:06:47,440
Do what?

1201
01:06:47,440 --> 01:06:48,440
You probably weren't hard on him.

1202
01:06:48,440 --> 01:06:51,000
I wasn't here, but he told you about it.

1203
01:06:51,000 --> 01:06:52,000
Yeah, he talked about it.

1204
01:06:52,000 --> 01:06:55,040
Can you tell us what he said to you or what you know about it?

1205
01:06:55,040 --> 01:06:56,040
Yeah.

1206
01:06:56,040 --> 01:07:06,400
That's the first time, you know, the racial climate was changing.

1207
01:07:06,400 --> 01:07:09,360
You know, the tension was rising.

1208
01:07:09,360 --> 01:07:16,960
And this friendly atmosphere that we once had there was disappearing.

1209
01:07:16,960 --> 01:07:20,920
Now he is how I experienced it.

1210
01:07:20,920 --> 01:07:23,480
I went in Air Force 1951.

1211
01:07:23,520 --> 01:07:29,440
I came home around 1955 at that time after I had re-enlisted and chose Air Force as a

1212
01:07:29,440 --> 01:07:30,440
career.

1213
01:07:30,440 --> 01:07:33,840
And I was a staff sergeant, did well during my first investment.

1214
01:07:33,840 --> 01:07:38,800
And I stopped at the local white grocery store that had been in the community before

1215
01:07:38,800 --> 01:07:44,040
my dead bill, too, because we had a relationship with that family, because that's where we did

1216
01:07:44,040 --> 01:07:45,560
our trading.

1217
01:07:45,560 --> 01:07:47,040
And I stopped there to get some gas.

1218
01:07:47,040 --> 01:07:53,360
Now I went in with a real friendly atmosphere and the wife of the store owner, she

1219
01:07:53,360 --> 01:08:00,160
was there and I spoke to her and they had one son and he was several years younger than

1220
01:08:00,160 --> 01:08:03,720
me, but I saw him grow up.

1221
01:08:03,720 --> 01:08:06,400
So I asked her, I said, well, where is your son?

1222
01:08:06,400 --> 01:08:09,560
I called him by his name and she said, you mean Mr.

1223
01:08:09,560 --> 01:08:11,120
Someone's Son?

1224
01:08:11,120 --> 01:08:16,400
Well, here I am now 25 years old, 26.

1225
01:08:16,400 --> 01:08:22,920
And she want me to call us on who's probably still a teenager, Mr. Never saw that before.

1226
01:08:23,880 --> 01:08:30,120
And I stopped at another grocery store in the community on down, coming toward Hattiesburg

1227
01:08:30,120 --> 01:08:32,280
where we would stop occasionally.

1228
01:08:32,280 --> 01:08:36,960
And I went in there just to buy something because I feel comfortable being at home and

1229
01:08:36,960 --> 01:08:41,160
the grocery store owner there, he said, oh, you're in there?

1230
01:08:41,160 --> 01:08:43,640
You're up now, and I said, yes I am.

1231
01:08:43,640 --> 01:08:50,280
I was stationed in Nebraska, Omaha, and off of Air Force Base.

1232
01:08:50,280 --> 01:08:53,680
And he says, what's it like being up there?

1233
01:08:53,680 --> 01:08:54,680
Okay?

1234
01:08:54,680 --> 01:08:56,480
Are they different?

1235
01:08:56,480 --> 01:08:57,480
Okay.

1236
01:08:57,480 --> 01:09:03,280
So he was quizzing me on my being outside of that in Mississippi environment.

1237
01:09:03,280 --> 01:09:04,280
Have you been growing?

1238
01:09:04,280 --> 01:09:09,080
And how had it affected me being in a more integrated area?

1239
01:09:09,080 --> 01:09:10,960
And I picked up on that immediately.

1240
01:09:10,960 --> 01:09:13,840
He was wanting to know if you've been ruined or not.

1241
01:09:13,840 --> 01:09:16,920
I'd been ruined, that's exactly right.

1242
01:09:16,920 --> 01:09:23,720
So that's how I knew then that the things had changed and my dad was getting into a situation.

1243
01:09:23,720 --> 01:09:29,320
But I didn't really focus on it because it had not been any open violence.

1244
01:09:29,320 --> 01:09:36,600
It was just a rise in the recognition that things about to happen in Mississippi now that

1245
01:09:36,600 --> 01:09:39,480
the mass does not want to happen.

1246
01:09:39,480 --> 01:09:44,680
And you're not going to be treated quite as kindly and as friendly as it was because

1247
01:09:44,680 --> 01:09:48,280
now you're starting to threaten our way of life.

1248
01:09:48,280 --> 01:09:49,520
And I had to look back on it.

1249
01:09:49,520 --> 01:09:51,760
I didn't recognize it at that time.

1250
01:09:51,760 --> 01:09:56,760
So what I did then was I didn't go into these places.

1251
01:09:56,760 --> 01:09:58,600
I just kind of stayed away from them.

1252
01:09:58,600 --> 01:09:59,600
Yeah.

1253
01:09:59,600 --> 01:10:02,960
Did your father talk to you about the changing atmosphere?

1254
01:10:02,960 --> 01:10:06,080
Did you just know it from your own experience?

1255
01:10:06,080 --> 01:10:09,320
When I would visit home, he didn't have to say it.

1256
01:10:09,320 --> 01:10:10,320
He was obvious.

1257
01:10:10,320 --> 01:10:11,320
Yeah.

1258
01:10:11,320 --> 01:10:13,840
And I was obvious.

1259
01:10:13,840 --> 01:10:18,840
He would, for example, I came home with my family at that time because I had a couple of kids

1260
01:10:18,840 --> 01:10:20,960
and we stayed there with him.

1261
01:10:20,960 --> 01:10:27,200
And he says, hey, be careful where you go and you hear.

1262
01:10:27,200 --> 01:10:32,000
At night time, we don't walk and get in front of windows.

1263
01:10:32,000 --> 01:10:34,920
And also we've seen some harassment here.

1264
01:10:34,920 --> 01:10:38,560
There was a gun in that room where you're going to be.

1265
01:10:38,560 --> 01:10:41,080
If you hear anything, hey, be aware of it.

1266
01:10:41,640 --> 01:10:44,280
Well, being military, that was a big deal.

1267
01:10:44,280 --> 01:10:45,880
Come out of the family, we had guns.

1268
01:10:45,880 --> 01:10:46,640
Hey, that's okay.

1269
01:10:46,640 --> 01:10:48,480
I'm comfortable with that environment.

1270
01:10:48,480 --> 01:10:51,080
So I saw the difference happening then.

1271
01:10:51,080 --> 01:10:54,000
It's a real change to have to take all those precautions.

1272
01:10:54,000 --> 01:10:55,560
They have to take all those precautions.

1273
01:10:55,560 --> 01:10:56,840
That is exactly right.

1274
01:10:57,880 --> 01:10:58,560
Sure.

1275
01:10:58,560 --> 01:11:01,520
Can you tell me about your own military experience?

1276
01:11:01,520 --> 01:11:03,640
What happened when you got drafted?

1277
01:11:03,640 --> 01:11:11,000
What I happened when I got drafted was it was doing the height of the Korean War.

1278
01:11:11,000 --> 01:11:13,720
And there was troops everywhere.

1279
01:11:13,720 --> 01:11:16,160
And when I'm in my everywhere, you know,

1280
01:11:16,160 --> 01:11:18,480
when you get into that military environment.

1281
01:11:18,480 --> 01:11:26,480
And I left home on a bus and went to Jackson along with some other recruits.

1282
01:11:26,480 --> 01:11:31,200
Went to the recruiting stand, at the reporting place.

1283
01:11:31,200 --> 01:11:38,800
And it was on a tri-state bus, a great one, on the other.

1284
01:11:38,800 --> 01:11:42,520
And there were whites and black guys on there.

1285
01:11:42,520 --> 01:11:44,480
And maybe some other passengers don't remember exactly.

1286
01:11:44,480 --> 01:11:48,280
But we got there and checked in.

1287
01:11:48,280 --> 01:11:49,520
The day was far along.

1288
01:11:49,520 --> 01:11:52,000
They gave us some food and took us to Motel.

1289
01:11:53,480 --> 01:11:54,960
Well, there was no Motel for whites.

1290
01:11:54,960 --> 01:11:56,240
We went out on Ferris Street.

1291
01:11:56,240 --> 01:11:59,000
That was a black hotel down there, okay?

1292
01:11:59,000 --> 01:12:01,160
Well, I'd been on Ferris Street, so, yeah, I'm all right.

1293
01:12:01,160 --> 01:12:02,160
We're free.

1294
01:12:02,160 --> 01:12:04,760
And the white ones, they went.

1295
01:12:04,760 --> 01:12:07,640
And the next morning got up and they picked us up in the bus and

1296
01:12:07,680 --> 01:12:09,760
scared us to the induction center.

1297
01:12:09,760 --> 01:12:12,600
And that's when the processing took place, you know,

1298
01:12:12,600 --> 01:12:16,720
along stripping down, doing your physicals and all.

1299
01:12:16,720 --> 01:12:18,320
And getting rid of the ship us off.

1300
01:12:18,320 --> 01:12:20,000
From there, the next day, we left, no,

1301
01:12:20,000 --> 01:12:22,480
we ended up with the San Antonio, Texas.

1302
01:12:22,480 --> 01:12:26,600
The lack of an Air Force base, which is a major Air Force training base.

1303
01:12:26,600 --> 01:12:29,880
And now I mean, there were troops all over the place.

1304
01:12:29,880 --> 01:12:34,880
And we were sleeping in tents because the permanent structures were all full.

1305
01:12:34,880 --> 01:12:38,160
And I'm gonna stay there just about three weeks.

1306
01:12:38,160 --> 01:12:41,280
And they keep us busy, guys busy.

1307
01:12:43,920 --> 01:12:48,080
Most of what got up, dressed, do your military thing.

1308
01:12:48,080 --> 01:12:50,920
And they've got and picked up big rocks, put them on pile.

1309
01:12:51,920 --> 01:12:54,760
And then the next day we'd come along and we'd pick up the smaller ones,

1310
01:12:54,760 --> 01:12:56,600
put them in piles, okay?

1311
01:12:56,600 --> 01:12:57,720
Let's keep it busy.

1312
01:12:57,720 --> 01:12:59,600
You thought I'm kidding, that's a fact.

1313
01:12:59,600 --> 01:13:03,040
All right, and then during the night, they spread them all out again and whatever.

1314
01:13:03,040 --> 01:13:03,880
All right.

1315
01:13:04,600 --> 01:13:07,360
But anyway, you went through all that stuff, you know,

1316
01:13:07,360 --> 01:13:10,320
my mom and my 22 years old, been working on the fall.

1317
01:13:10,320 --> 01:13:12,320
Yeah, I'm not yet picking up rocks.

1318
01:13:13,320 --> 01:13:15,480
And then we went on a ship,

1319
01:13:15,480 --> 01:13:19,200
this out there, a ship with Air Force base in Wichita Falls, Texas.

1320
01:13:19,200 --> 01:13:21,120
That's why I did my basic training.

1321
01:13:21,120 --> 01:13:26,640
From basic training, I was assigned to French and Seymour and Air Base

1322
01:13:26,640 --> 01:13:30,360
in Cheyenne, Wyoming, for my tech training.

1323
01:13:30,440 --> 01:13:36,040
And that was a tele-type training school there,

1324
01:13:36,040 --> 01:13:39,080
along with other training facilities too,

1325
01:13:39,080 --> 01:13:41,200
for in the communications field.

1326
01:13:41,200 --> 01:13:43,520
And there was a motor transportation and bigot,

1327
01:13:43,520 --> 01:13:45,840
then kids had to drive trucks and stuff.

1328
01:13:45,840 --> 01:13:48,960
Let me ask you, so how did you feel about being drafted?

1329
01:13:51,080 --> 01:13:52,720
I tried to try my best day out of it.

1330
01:13:52,720 --> 01:13:54,880
My dad tried to get me deferred.

1331
01:13:54,880 --> 01:13:56,840
And I didn't want to go.

1332
01:13:56,840 --> 01:13:58,560
No, I did not want to go.

1333
01:13:58,600 --> 01:14:02,360
All because I'm comfortable where I am.

1334
01:14:02,360 --> 01:14:03,480
Yeah.

1335
01:14:03,480 --> 01:14:07,760
What about were you drafted specifically into the Air Force?

1336
01:14:07,760 --> 01:14:08,840
Or did you have any say?

1337
01:14:08,840 --> 01:14:10,160
Oh, that's the piece I missed.

1338
01:14:10,160 --> 01:14:11,560
No, let me tell you how that happened.

1339
01:14:11,560 --> 01:14:13,080
All right.

1340
01:14:13,080 --> 01:14:18,200
One, there may be a little month, a little over,

1341
01:14:20,200 --> 01:14:23,880
proud to going in the Air Force.

1342
01:14:23,960 --> 01:14:28,560
I received a letter from the,

1343
01:14:31,880 --> 01:14:33,640
that'll name, Local Boy.

1344
01:14:33,640 --> 01:14:34,440
The draft boy?

1345
01:14:34,440 --> 01:14:36,200
Brack Boy.

1346
01:14:36,200 --> 01:14:39,600
Directing the I report for induction

1347
01:14:39,600 --> 01:14:43,200
on the 15th of September, 1951.

1348
01:14:44,320 --> 01:14:45,920
And I looked at it and I said,

1349
01:14:45,920 --> 01:14:48,560
okay, well, I'm getting ready to get out of here.

1350
01:14:48,560 --> 01:14:50,800
So I'm living in the house of my dad,

1351
01:14:50,800 --> 01:14:53,320
and I told him, hey, this is what this is about.

1352
01:14:53,320 --> 01:14:58,160
So I start preparing to go off to the Army.

1353
01:14:58,160 --> 01:15:00,120
Because that's where the guys were going, right?

1354
01:15:02,680 --> 01:15:06,120
My uncle, my dad's baby sister's husband

1355
01:15:06,120 --> 01:15:11,120
was in the 92nd Infantry in Italy,

1356
01:15:13,320 --> 01:15:16,760
a ground foot soldier, fault.

1357
01:15:16,760 --> 01:15:20,080
And I told him, he said, no, no, you don't want to do that.

1358
01:15:20,080 --> 01:15:20,840
Uh-oh.

1359
01:15:20,840 --> 01:15:22,920
Then I had a couple of other black guys in the community

1360
01:15:22,920 --> 01:15:25,840
that was in combat, he said, you don't want to do that.

1361
01:15:25,840 --> 01:15:28,920
He said, hey, go to the Navy or the Air Force.

1362
01:15:28,920 --> 01:15:31,200
Don't get caught up in this Army thing.

1363
01:15:31,200 --> 01:15:33,800
And after they told me that, I said, okay.

1364
01:15:33,800 --> 01:15:38,800
So I procrastinated up until the 10th of September.

1365
01:15:38,800 --> 01:15:40,960
You didn't give yourself much?

1366
01:15:40,960 --> 01:15:41,960
No.

1367
01:15:41,960 --> 01:15:44,760
And I said, look, I got to make up a man.

1368
01:15:44,760 --> 01:15:46,640
So I went to the Air Force Recruiter.

1369
01:15:46,640 --> 01:15:49,400
He enhanced bird is in the basement of the old post office,

1370
01:15:49,400 --> 01:15:50,680
downtown, yeah.

1371
01:15:50,680 --> 01:15:53,920
And I walked in and there was an Air Force Recruiter,

1372
01:15:53,920 --> 01:15:56,520
armor recruiter, Navy Recruiter.

1373
01:15:56,520 --> 01:15:58,320
I'm not sure whether they had a Marine or not.

1374
01:15:58,320 --> 01:16:01,080
And I saw the Air Force not winning that door.

1375
01:16:01,080 --> 01:16:03,200
And that sergeancy said, can I help you?

1376
01:16:03,200 --> 01:16:06,320
Now, I told him, I said, I like to volunteer for the Air Force.

1377
01:16:06,320 --> 01:16:08,760
So he gave me some papers that fell out and, you know,

1378
01:16:08,760 --> 01:16:11,160
and I took some tests of whatever.

1379
01:16:11,160 --> 01:16:13,640
And he said, well, when you want to leave,

1380
01:16:13,640 --> 01:16:14,960
I said, can I leave today?

1381
01:16:14,960 --> 01:16:19,400
He said, no, the bus is already gone.

1382
01:16:19,400 --> 01:16:20,560
He said, we're about in the morning,

1383
01:16:20,560 --> 01:16:21,600
be down here at seven o'clock.

1384
01:16:21,600 --> 01:16:23,520
I said, OK, I'll be here.

1385
01:16:23,520 --> 01:16:26,000
So at seven o'clock, I reported to the post office,

1386
01:16:26,000 --> 01:16:28,280
and they were there and they carried us down to the bus station,

1387
01:16:28,280 --> 01:16:31,280
which is they all walked north street, you know,

1388
01:16:31,280 --> 01:16:33,800
called a bus out the Jackson.

1389
01:16:33,800 --> 01:16:43,240
And so after I got situated at Shepherd Air Force Base

1390
01:16:43,240 --> 01:16:47,280
in basic training, which is in Wichita Falls, Texas.

1391
01:16:47,280 --> 01:16:51,840
And that was it, by the way, in the early part of September

1392
01:16:51,840 --> 01:17:01,960
of 1951, I was in my unit and my squad drilling with them

1393
01:17:01,960 --> 01:17:06,400
out on the parade field going through my training.

1394
01:17:06,400 --> 01:17:12,360
And in that group, we must have been about 30 guys

1395
01:17:12,360 --> 01:17:15,520
in these squads.

1396
01:17:15,520 --> 01:17:19,800
My name came out over the PA system,

1397
01:17:19,800 --> 01:17:24,600
private Vernon, Dameron, Jr. report to the order room.

1398
01:17:24,600 --> 01:17:26,520
I'm 22 years old.

1399
01:17:26,520 --> 01:17:30,880
I'm in there with a bunch of guys, not 18, 19, maybe 20.

1400
01:17:30,880 --> 01:17:32,960
I'm kind of like the old dude, OK?

1401
01:17:32,960 --> 01:17:35,280
Never a few left over in World War II.

1402
01:17:35,280 --> 01:17:37,840
You know, that was coming back again.

1403
01:17:37,840 --> 01:17:39,520
And but not very many.

1404
01:17:39,520 --> 01:17:42,520
I don't know if it was one of them out, but anyway, I was

1405
01:17:42,520 --> 01:17:44,280
saying, what have I done now?

1406
01:17:44,280 --> 01:17:47,120
Because I'm in this middle-aged environment now.

1407
01:17:47,120 --> 01:17:48,240
Your name come out.

1408
01:17:48,240 --> 01:17:50,840
You don't remember anything that you did.

1409
01:17:50,840 --> 01:17:52,440
What have I done?

1410
01:17:52,440 --> 01:17:53,440
Right.

1411
01:17:53,440 --> 01:17:56,160
And so squadly to call to a hall.

1412
01:17:56,160 --> 01:18:00,040
This miss me from the group told me report to the order room.

1413
01:18:00,040 --> 01:18:03,640
I went to the order room, reported to the first sergeant.

1414
01:18:03,640 --> 01:18:04,400
He's two gentlemen.

1415
01:18:04,400 --> 01:18:05,760
I won't talk with you.

1416
01:18:05,760 --> 01:18:08,200
They went to me in clothes.

1417
01:18:08,200 --> 01:18:10,280
And they asked me, your name?

1418
01:18:10,280 --> 01:18:12,160
I told them burn up, they were junior.

1419
01:18:12,160 --> 01:18:13,800
Let me see your dog tags.

1420
01:18:13,800 --> 01:18:15,720
Dog tags, romma, they put them in dog tags out.

1421
01:18:15,720 --> 01:18:17,160
And they checked them.

1422
01:18:17,160 --> 01:18:18,960
That's who you are.

1423
01:18:18,960 --> 01:18:24,120
He said, you know your draft Dodger.

1424
01:18:24,120 --> 01:18:25,280
No sir.

1425
01:18:25,280 --> 01:18:26,480
I didn't know that.

1426
01:18:26,480 --> 01:18:30,120
Well, didn't you get your notice from the local board?

1427
01:18:30,120 --> 01:18:31,080
Lion's room and team.

1428
01:18:31,080 --> 01:18:33,560
No sir.

1429
01:18:33,560 --> 01:18:35,760
I didn't sign for it.

1430
01:18:35,760 --> 01:18:38,560
Lion stood in flat foot.

1431
01:18:38,560 --> 01:18:41,720
And he said, well, they sent you one.

1432
01:18:41,720 --> 01:18:43,760
I said, no sir, I never got it.

1433
01:18:43,760 --> 01:18:46,120
He said, well, OK.

1434
01:18:46,120 --> 01:18:47,200
You already in now.

1435
01:18:47,200 --> 01:18:48,120
I guess that's all right.

1436
01:18:48,120 --> 01:18:49,560
Well, I guess it is all right.

1437
01:18:49,560 --> 01:18:51,440
You're going to take me out and put me in the army?

1438
01:18:51,440 --> 01:18:52,680
I wasn't thinking that for him.

1439
01:18:52,680 --> 01:18:54,040
I'm thinking that now.

1440
01:18:54,040 --> 01:18:58,000
And when we did that, well, the press variation dried up.

1441
01:18:58,000 --> 01:18:59,920
And I got a hold of my nerves.

1442
01:18:59,920 --> 01:19:02,440
And the first sergeant said, all right, get back to your unit.

1443
01:19:02,440 --> 01:19:03,640
I went back to my unit.

1444
01:19:03,640 --> 01:19:06,040
Did you know that that might happen?

1445
01:19:06,040 --> 01:19:08,720
Or did you just know that was going to happen?

1446
01:19:08,720 --> 01:19:09,720
No.

1447
01:19:09,720 --> 01:19:11,960
And then he just flashed the badges on me.

1448
01:19:11,960 --> 01:19:14,400
So they were from some kind of investigative unit.

1449
01:19:14,400 --> 01:19:17,360
I don't know whether with the FBI or the local arm

1450
01:19:17,360 --> 01:19:20,800
investigators, you know, their own investigators.

1451
01:19:20,800 --> 01:19:21,760
But no, they were federal.

1452
01:19:21,760 --> 01:19:22,520
I know that though.

1453
01:19:22,520 --> 01:19:24,480
They had a federal.

1454
01:19:24,480 --> 01:19:26,280
That's a little nerve-wracking.

1455
01:19:26,280 --> 01:19:27,040
Would all of them.

1456
01:19:27,040 --> 01:19:29,800
And you came up with that?

1457
01:19:29,800 --> 01:19:30,880
On your feet.

1458
01:19:30,880 --> 01:19:31,880
Oh my.

1459
01:19:31,880 --> 01:19:32,880
You don't be in 22 years old.

1460
01:19:32,880 --> 01:19:34,080
You learn how to lie.

1461
01:19:34,080 --> 01:19:35,600
You learn how to lie quick.

1462
01:19:35,600 --> 01:19:36,600
Especially when you get in the band.

1463
01:19:36,600 --> 01:19:38,080
It sounds like it came in handy.

1464
01:19:38,080 --> 01:19:38,600
Yes, it is.

1465
01:19:38,600 --> 01:19:39,360
That's a good skill.

1466
01:19:39,360 --> 01:19:40,360
I guess.

1467
01:19:40,360 --> 01:19:41,360
Yeah, very good.

1468
01:19:41,360 --> 01:19:42,360
It worked.

1469
01:19:42,360 --> 01:19:46,760
When you went into the military, how did you end up?

1470
01:19:46,760 --> 01:19:49,600
You said you went to the communication school for teletype training.

1471
01:19:49,600 --> 01:19:51,880
How did that come about?

1472
01:19:51,880 --> 01:19:55,640
That's another phase that's very interesting.

1473
01:19:55,640 --> 01:20:02,560
I was assigned to Fransity One Air Base in Chiang Wai-Homie and to become a teletype operator.

1474
01:20:02,560 --> 01:20:09,160
Being raised on a farm, or we had an old cash register.

1475
01:20:09,160 --> 01:20:13,280
My dad found somewhere and it was manual.

1476
01:20:13,280 --> 01:20:18,740
And now you're taking this farm, boy, who's going to use the drive in trucks, hauling logs,

1477
01:20:18,740 --> 01:20:20,960
running tractor and all this.

1478
01:20:20,960 --> 01:20:27,500
Yes, I had mechanical abilities, operation type, operating type abilities, but not for no

1479
01:20:27,500 --> 01:20:29,000
typewriter, no teletype.

1480
01:20:29,000 --> 01:20:30,000
Yeah.

1481
01:20:30,000 --> 01:20:31,800
No typewriter.

1482
01:20:31,800 --> 01:20:37,760
And they assigned me that school and I started off and after that for a while, I was in this

1483
01:20:37,760 --> 01:20:43,000
typing class, J-U-G-S-F-G-F-S-F.

1484
01:20:43,000 --> 01:20:47,920
And I'm telling myself I don't want to be in a teletype operator.

1485
